FIFA Player Analysis using Linear Regression
📌 Overview

This project performs an in-depth analysis of FIFA player data to uncover patterns, trends, and relationships between player attributes and overall performance. The primary focus is on applying Linear Regression to predict player ratings based on key features.

📂 Dataset
Source: FIFA player dataset
Contains ~89 attributes including:
Player details (Name, Age, Nationality, Club)
Performance metrics (Overall, Potential)
Skill attributes (Dribbling, Passing, Shooting, etc.)
Physical attributes (Height, Weight, Strength)


🎯 Objectives
Perform data cleaning and preprocessing
Explore player statistics using EDA (Exploratory Data Analysis)
Identify key features impacting player performance
Build a Linear Regression model to predict player ratings
Evaluate model performance using standard metrics


🛠️ Technologies Used
Python 🐍
Pandas & NumPy
Matplotlib & Seaborn
Scikit-learn


📊 Key Steps
1. Data Preprocessing
Removed unnecessary columns
Handled missing values
Converted categorical data into numerical format


2. Exploratory Data Analysis
Distribution of player ratings
Correlation between attributes
Age vs Performance analysis


3. Feature Selection
Selected important attributes like:
Dribbling
Ball Control
Reactions
Finishing
Passing

4. Model Building
Applied Linear Regression
Split dataset into training and testing sets


5. Model Evaluation
Metrics used:
Mean Absolute Error (MAE)
Mean Squared Error (MSE)
R² Score


📈 Results
The model shows a strong relationship between technical skills and overall rating
Attributes like Reactions, Ball Control, and Passing have high impact
Linear Regression provides a good baseline prediction model


💡 Insights
Younger players tend to have higher potential than current ratings
Skill-based attributes influence ratings more than physical attributes
High correlation exists between technical skills


